Natural Oil field Services Limited (NOSL) and the Nigeria Petroleum Development Corporation (NPDC) have donated an ambulance and other medical supplies to the Akwa Ibom State Government, with a view to combating the Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic. Other items donated by the two oil firms include surgical face mask, zinc oxide, adhesive strip plaster, examination gloves, surgical gown, hand sanitizers, face mask (non-surgical) , first aid box, oxygen cylinder, oxygen face mask, infra-red thermometer and stretcher. The items were received in Uyo by the Secretary to the state government, Chief Emmanuel Ekuwem. Presenting the items, the NPDC Managing Director, Engr. Mansur Sambo who was represented by the NPDC’s Deputy Manager, Community Relations, Mr. David Arijoba, commended the state government’s efforts in combating the COVID -19 pandemic and noted that the presentation of the ambulance and other medical supplies was imperative at this time. He said: “We the management of the Nigerian Petroleum Development Company (NPDC), a subsidiary of Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) and the management of Naturals Oilfield Services Limited (NOSL), a subsidiary of Sterling Oil Group are here to show our solidarity to the government and people of Akwa Ibom State in the fight against this virus”.  NPDC donates protective, medical equipment to Edo govt Redeemed Church donates COVID-19 medical supplies NNPC, 31 upstream operators earmark N11bn to combat COVID-19